NORTH CHARLESTON, S.C. (WCIV) -- The teen accused in the{}shooting death of a{}15-year-old boy Thursday evening in North Charleston faced a bond court judge Friday morning.Police charged 19-year-old Deandre C. Michael with involuntary manslaughter. He was given a $250,000 bond.{}
According to North Charleston police, officers were sent to the 7400 block of Northside Drive around 6 p.m. Thursday to treat a teen suffering from a gunshot wound.{}
When officers arrived, they found the teen sitting in the passenger seat of a car. EMS crews arrived and tried to treat the teen, but he later died, officials said.{}
Court documents released Friday during a bond hearing identify the fatally wounded teen as Hasnai Davis.
Witnesses told investigators that the victim was with three other people in the car at a restaurant on Ashley Phosphate Road when one of the people in the car who was handling a gun accidentally fired the weapon.
The driver left the area and drove to Northside Drive, police said, adding that the suspect tossed the gun out of the car. Officers searching the area recovered it, however.{}
Police say they are still investigating the shooting.
